title: VP, Head of Enterprise Architecture, Research, and Developer Experience
description:
About Ford

 Job Description 

Come help build a better world, where every person is free to move and pursue their dreams. Ford Motor Company was built on the belief that freedom of movement drives human progress. It’s a belief that has fueled our passion to create great cars and trucks. And today, it drives our commitment to become the world’s most trusted mobility company, designing vehicles for a smart world that helps people move more safely, confidently, and freely. Ford is experiencing significant business transformation in an ever-changing digital world. We are dedicated to delivering distinctive products and solutions, having an “always on” relationship with customers and continuously improving our user experience.

Since 1959, Ford Credit has worked with dealerships to put people behind the wheels of great Ford and Lincoln vehicles. We provide financing, outstanding service and professional expertise to five thousand dealers and more than four million customers in at least 100 countries. Prospective employees can expect a professional atmosphere with opportunities to grow.

What You’ll Be Able To Do

AstheHead of Enterprise Architecture, Research, & Developer Experience, you will lead a team of 200+ experienced technical professionals (Architects, Developer Experience, Research Labs Scientist) to design Ford Credit enterprise architecture, transform Ford Credit software engineering practice, and research cutting edge technology. This opportunity will report to Saurabh Raisinghani, Chief Technology Officer.

In addition, you will:

Define global systems and application architecture for Model E, Ford Pro FinSimple and Ford Blue products
Lead the design of multi-year technology roadmap, outlining the core technology needed to execute Model E business model as well as run Ford Credit’s current business model
Modernize large global Ford Credit footprint into a cloud-first model using Google Cloud Platform, effectively enabling cloud-native business solutions.
Partner and guide application, infrastructure, security, and Product teams to define, design, and deliver technical roadmaps and architecture patterns that enable the business while aligning with Ford Credit strategic objectives
Build a high functioning architecture that provide high level of partnership to the Engineering Digital Product and Platform teams
Provide strategic thought leadership to Engineering and Business teams
Provide constructive peer review feedback for product ideas submitted from other areas of the organization
Continue to evolve the organization in support of the PDO model and use of Agile methods
Work with lead Product Owner matched pair to coordinate quarterly prioritization process while delivering the quarterly OKRs
Work with security, infrastructure, and SRE teams to implement DevOps and lead the automation of infrastructure deployments and ensure security and compliance
Promote technical delivery of large-scale projects on all infrastructure technologies
Ensure that technology delivery meets policy, regulatory, architectural and security standards
Verify that the delivered software group products meet desired encryption, security, and business outcomes.
Provide industry thought leadership for Policies, Processes, People and Tools, while driving a software development lifecycle.


Basic Qualifications

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering or Electrical Engineer
10+ years of progressively Enterprise Architecture and/or DevOps leadership experiences with large scale outcomes aimed at consumers.


Preferred Qualifications

Demonstrated technical vision with strong DevSecOps expertise across large-scale Agile teams. Ability to identify key drivers, core assumptions, and significant trends across a complex, competitive landscape.
Proven experience in leveraging digital, big data, cloud, and AI (Artificial Intelligence) for competitive advantage
Experience leading teams of greater than 100 people
Experience with formulating vision and strategy to transform, simplify, and modernize the implementation of customer-facing capabilities
Experience with underlying application program (API) methods for systems integrations/data exchanges
Coordination, integration, and testing activities within and outside of the product line
Operational experience supporting systems in a 24*7 “always on” environment
Defining analytics to be collected regarding the product, and prioritization of their collection


What We Can Offer

As part of the Ford family, you’ll enjoy excellent compensation, and a comprehensive benefits package that includes generous PTO, retirement, savings and stock investment plans, incentive compensation, and much more. You’ll also experience exciting opportunities for professional and personal growth and recognition.

Candidates for positions with Ford Motor Company must be legally authorized to work in the U.S. Verification of employment eligibility will be required at time of hire. Visa sponsorship is not available for this position.

Ford Motor Company is an equal opportunity employer committed to a culturally diverse workforce. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, age, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability status or protected veteran status.

At Ford, the health and safety of our employees is our top priority. Vaccination has been proven to play a critical role in combatting COVID-19. As a result, Ford has made the decision to require U.S. salaried employees to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19, unless employees require an accommodation for religious or medical reasons. Being fully vaccinated means that an individual is at least two weeks past their final dose of an authorized COVID-19 vaccine regimen. As a condition of employment, newly hired employees will be required to provide proof of their COVID-19 vaccination or an approved medical or religious exemption.

 Location 

Dearborn, MI, United States

prompt: I would like a job in Eastern Europe at a Technical Company. I have experiene as a Director and work largely in Sales, Consulting, and Job-Planning.
title: Director, Large Customer Sales, Central and Eastern Europe
description:
Note: By applying to this position you will have an opportunity to share your preferred working location from the following: Warsaw, Poland; Budapest, Hungary; Bucharest, Romania.

Minimum qualifications:
Bachelor's degree in Marketing, Business Management, or equivalent practical experience.
Experience in C-level customer sales.
Experience in sales mentoring, leading, and developing an executive-led team.
Ability to speak and write in English fluently.


Preferred qualifications:
Experience in an advertising sales or business development role.
Experience working across multiple markets in large organizations.
Experience leading decentralized teams, mentoring, and developing talent.
Advertising experience from the advertiser, agency, or other media owner side.
Knowledge of Google’s advertising products and their applications.
Ability to use stakeholder management and prioritization skills.


About The Job

As Central and Eastern European (CEE) Client Solutions Director, you will manage the team for high performance, help lead transformational project proposals and solutions with customers while mentoring for career development. You will join C-level meetings as an expert to describe the value of products and solutions. You will also be the representative to EMEA and Global product teams to help develop these business areas in CEE. You will also partner closely with the regional management to help shape and jointly execute on the product business strategy.

Our Large Customer Sales teams partner closely with many of the world’s biggest advertisers and agencies to develop digital solutions that build businesses and brands. We enjoy a bird’s eye view on the massive transformation occurring as advertising shifts to mobile and online platforms. We're uniquely situated to help shape how companies grow their businesses in the digital age. We advise clients on Google's broad range of products across search, video and mobile to help them connect instantly and seamlessly with their audiences.

Responsibilities

Work with executive leaders and managers across the region and functions on defining and prioritizing the local product-levers and needs, while translating global priorities into regional strategy.
Partner with external customers and agencies on strategic and complex solutions and technologies. Mentor Product Specialists in day-to-day work, help remove structural bottlenecks, and manage their performance.
Represent CEE in the EMEA/Global product councils, connecting and sharing best practices with other Product Specialist leads.
Work with Product Specialist to ensure they have a meaningful development plan for their career and capabilities.


Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form .

prompt: I am a former Director looking for a job on the East Coast. My strenghts are in strategy as I have a MBA degree,
title: Head of Buyer Experience COE
description:
Responsible for strategy, design, and implementation of a new approach to the Wipro client experience. Through a combined focus on developing a centers of expertise (COE) that would create a deeper level of access to Wipro expertise and the creation of supporting materials, the role will seek to build a stronger level of alliance and coordination between sales and marketing via a design-centric, strategic approach. 





Initially focused on high-value client pursuits the role will look to broaden, expand and productize learnings while establishing new engagement methods across the range of opportunities and industries. The role will be strategic to the current Wipro transformation from creation of story narratives to empowering our client-facing Wipro employees abilities to interpret and engage with clients on a deeper, more strategic level and in the market. 











Build a Buyer Experience COE to create a series of quality, consistent communications at every touchpoint that align to our brand message.


Sales Assets and Content Management
Theme Development, Story Telling, Design Thinking
Buyer Experience Design across all Touchpoints
Proposal Production (and the framework governance)









Requirements


Buyer Experience CoE head, Band D2
Sales Content Management lead + existing catalyst team
Story Telling / Design Thinking Professionals
Proposal Production Resources, possibly internal

prompt: I want a job on the East Coast in an Executive Role. I majored in Finance and am looking for a full-time job.
title: Operational Risk Director - Enterprise Functions
description:
About This Role

Wells Fargo is seeking an Operational Risk Director to oversee Wells Fargo Technology Enterprise Functions (i.e., Finance, Chief Operating Office, Human Resources, Public Affairs, Corporate Risk, and Legal) on risk generated activities. This risk oversight leadership is expected to collaborate closely with the respective Operational Risk Business Oversight leaders for applications as well as collaborate with Technology Infrastructure and Chief Technology Office Oversight leaders on the infrastructure supporting Enterprise Functions' applications.

In This Role, You Will
Provide vision and set direction for Operational Risk teams to achieve long-term strategic objectives that impact organization and management across functions
Manage the development, implementation, and monitoring of a risk-based program for a business or large functional area with moderate to high risk to identify, assess, and mitigate operational risk that arises from inadequate or failed internal processes, people, systems, or external events
Maintain a balance between risk mitigation and operational efficiency
Direct execution of major operational risk programs companywide or lines of businesses with significant risk and multiple, complex regulatory environments
Provide subject matter expertise across lines of business or directly manage enterprise controls for specific functional areas
Influence and provide input on policy, framework, and program development for related lines of business or companywide strategy
Ensure reporting, escalation, and remediation of issues, deficiencies or regulatory matters regarding operational risk to leaders, committees, and appropriate executive management
Identify programs or initiatives related to line of business and enterprise strategy with considerable impact companywide and externally
Collaborate and influence all levels of professionals including more experienced leaders
Lead team to achieve objectives
Manage communication and collaboration with business heads, Legal, Audit, and regulators on risk related topics
Manage allocation of people and financial resources for Operational Risk
Develop and guide a culture of talent development to meet business objectives and strategy
   Required Qualifications, US:  
8+ years of Operational Risk experience or equivalent experience demonstrated through one or a combination of the following: work experience, training, military experience, education
4+ years of Management experience
   Desired Qualifications:  
Extensive risk management or audit experiences in a senior management role
Strong executive presence with the ability to inspire a large and geographically dispersed organization.
Proven ability to establish a strategic vision and drive strong outcomes and results.
Demonstrated ability to influence and lead across first and second line of defenses while maintaining close relationships with third line of defenses.
Highly experienced in building and maintaining relationships with the regulators and ability to understand regulatory trends and expectations.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, inquisitive nature and comfort challenging current practices to drive efficiency and standardization.
Knowledge of technology and security organization practices, operations, risk management processes, principles, architectural requirements, including incident response methodologies. Additionally, practitioner experiences are desirable.
   Job Expectations:  
Managing a team of experienced Technology and Information Security risk professional in a global organization responsible for oversight on Chief Information Officers supporting Wells Fargo enterprise Functions.
Delivering and synthesizing technology and information security risks results by applying business risks acumen for the enterprise functions.
Build and maintain relationships with senior business and technology stakeholders by providing our independent risk assessments and ability to influence, advice, and counsel these stakeholders to focus on most prioritized risks presented in the businesses.
Ability to negotiate challenges to achieve best outcomes.
Working across the aisles and demonstrate leadership within Corporate Risk and Operational Risk Management globally to drive (and initiate if needed) collaboration and consistency on oversight activities and risk assessments.
Experienced in a strong escalation culture to drive consistent execution of a robust control environment and awareness within the senior management of the businesses.
Provide thought leadership by leading and guide teams through the complex changing environment in the organization.
Keeping abreast of industry trends and emerging risks and anticipate areas of focus and attention of regulators, keeping the business and corporate risk colleagues informed
  We Value Diversity 

At Wells Fargo, we believe in diversity, equity and inclusion in the workplace; accordingly, we welcome applications for employment from all qualified candidates, regardless of race, color, gender, national origin, religion, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, genetic information, individuals with disabilities, pregnancy, marital status, status as a protected veteran or any other status protected by applicable law.

Employees support our focus on building strong customer relationships balanced with a strong risk mitigating and compliance-driven culture which firmly establishes those disciplines as critical to the success of our customers and company. They are accountable for execution of all applicable risk programs (Credit, Market, Financial Crimes, Operational, Regulatory Compliance), which includes effectively following and adhering to applicable Wells Fargo policies and procedures, appropriately fulfilling risk and compliance obligations, timely and effective escalation and remediation of issues, and making sound risk decisions. There is emphasis on proactive monitoring, governance, risk identification and escalation, as well as making sound risk decisions commensurate with the business unit's risk appetite and all risk and compliance program requirements.

Candidates applying to job openings posted in US: All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran.

Candidates applying to job openings posted in Canada: Applications for employment are encouraged from all qualified candidates, including women, persons with disabilities, aboriginal peoples and visible minorities. Accommodation for applicants with disabilities is available upon request in connection with the recruitment process.

Reference Number

R-221205-1
